        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/8baadc/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2018-10-31T16:26:49.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I\u00b4m preparing a NSG Boudots (and VR Malconsorts) tasting next year.<br>\nNow I\u00b4ve got a bottle</p>\n<p>1986<br>\nNUITS-SAINT-GEORGES<br>\n\"\u201cLes Boudots\u201d Premier Cru<br>\nDomaine Noellat<br>\nMis en bouteille au Domaine<br>\nS\u00e9lectionn\u00e9 et distribu\u00e9<br>\npar L\u00c9GLISE &amp; FILS<br>\nBeaune - C\u00f4te d\u00b4Or - France</p>\n<p>Has anybody an idea from which Noellat this wine might be?<br>\nMichel Noellat? Georges Noellat? Charles Noellat (bought up by Leroy in 1988)?</p>\n<p>The wine seems to be bottled at the domaine, and bought in (unlabelled) bottles and labelled by the negociant L\u00c9GLISE &amp; FILS \u2026<br>\nSure I could remove the red (neutral) capsule to read the cork brand, but I very much doubt I will find more than<br>\n\u201cMis en bouteille au Domaine\u201d or \u201cMis en bouteille a la propriet\u00e9\u201d or \u201cMis en Domaine\u201d \u2026</p>\n<p>Did all of the producers above sell bottles to negociants? At last in a vintage like 1986 which wasn\u00b4t \u201creally great\u201d.</p>\n<p>The spelling \u201cLes Boudots\u201d and \u201cAux Boudots\u201d is interchangeable.<br>\nIt seems that all Noellats first used \u201cLes Boudots\u201d, but Georges N. changed to \u201cAux Boudots\u201d in 2011/12 (?) - and Michel Noellat in 2014/15 (?), no idea why.<br>\nSo this seems to be no help.</p>\n<p>Thanks.</p>",
