        "created_at": "2018-10-31T16:37:48.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"146934\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Yes, they were all selling to n\u00e9gociants back then. Wouldn\u2019t hold out too much hope for the bottle being that exciting though, given the producers and the vintage.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>The bottle looks fine, with perfect ruby colour and a level 1.5 cm below cork \u2026 so absolutely no reason why it shouldn\u00b4t be a least \u201cgood\u201d - and really mature \u2026 (although I never was a fan of the 1986 vintage \u2026 but I\u00b4ve had some excellent wines, e.g. a VR Beaumonts/Vasseur recently)</p>",
