      {
        "id": 2512873,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-10-31T16:46:06.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"146934\">\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"146934\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Yes, they were all selling to n\u00e9gociants back then. Wouldn\u2019t hold out too much hope for the bottle being that exciting though, given the producers and the vintage.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>The bottle looks fine, with perfect ruby colour and a level 1.5 cm below cork \u2026 so absolutely no reason why it shouldn\u00b4t be a least \u201cgood\u201d - and really mature \u2026 (although I never was a fan of the 1996 vintage \u2026 but I\u00b4ve had some excellent wines, e.g. a VR Beaumonts/Vasseur recently)</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>1996 or 1986?</p>\n<p>All the Noellats seem to have pretty fat-berried selections of Pinot Noir growing in Boudots, at least in so far as I\u2019ve been able to discover on foot, which combined with 1986 botrytis and high yields could be messy. 1996 perhaps more promising?</p>\n<p>Hope it\u2019s great!</p>",
