        "name": "Gerhard P.  (P r @ \u20ac s e n t)",
        "username": "Gerhard_P",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/8baadc/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2018-10-31T17:36:43.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"6\" data-topic=\"146934\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>I\u2019ve had a very nice 1993 Noellat from boudots\u2013don\u2019t have my notes at the moment, but I think it was Charles.  It was actually one of the top bottles in a horizontal about 3 years ago that included most major producers.  I would be a little nervous about an 86, but don\u2019t have any experience to report.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Hm, I don\u00b4t think it could have been a 1993 Charles Noellat \u2026 since Leroy bought up the domaine in 1988 \u2026 she also bought a substantial stock of older vintages, but used to relabel everything with \u201cMaison Leroy\u201d \u2026 and sold them at very high prices \u2026  <img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/2X/3/3d5d493eaefe29f8a37971ea1ffbb65a4e2b21aa.gif\" width=\"26\" height=\"23\" alt=\"[pwn.gif]\" title=\"pwn\"></p>\n<p>If it was a 1993 it was either Domaine Leroy (= ex-Charles Noellat vines) \u2026 or a different Noellat.</p>",
